.TH wxTextAttr 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxTextAttr \- \fIwxTextAttr\fR represents the character and paragraph attributes, or style, for a range of text in a \fIwxTextCtrl\fR or \fIwxRichTextCtrl\fR (not implemented in wx).

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
When setting up a \fIwxTextAttr\fR object, pass a bitlist mask to \fIsetFlags/2\fR to indicate which style elements should be changed. As a convenience, when you call a setter such as SetFont, the relevant bit will be set.

.PP
See: \fIwxTextCtrl\fR

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxTextAttr

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxTextAttr() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBdestroy(This :: wxTextAttr()) -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Destroys the object


.RE
.B
\fBgetAlignment(This) -> wx:wx_enum() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the alignment flags.

.PP
See ?wxTextAttrAlignment for a list of available styles.


.RE
.B
\fBgetBackgroundColour(This) -> wx:wx_colour4()\fR
\fB                             when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the background colour.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFlags(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns flags indicating which attributes are applicable.

.PP
See \fIsetFlags/2\fR for a list of available flags.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFont(This) -> wxFont:wxFont() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Creates and returns a font specified by the font attributes in the \fIwxTextAttr\fR object.

.PP
Note that \fIwxTextAttr\fR does not store a \fIwxFont\fR object, so this is only a temporary font.

.PP
For greater efficiency, access the font attributes directly.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFontEncoding(This) -> wx:wx_enum() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the font encoding.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFontFaceName(This) -> unicode:charlist()\fR
\fB                         when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the font face name.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFontSize(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the font size in points.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFontStyle(This) -> wx:wx_enum() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the font style.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFontUnderlined(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the font is underlined.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFontWeight(This) -> wx:wx_enum() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the font weight.


.RE
.B
\fBgetLeftIndent(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the left indent in tenths of a millimetre.


.RE
.B
\fBgetLeftSubIndent(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the left sub-indent in tenths of a millimetre.


.RE
.B
\fBgetRightIndent(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the right indent in tenths of a millimeter.


.RE
.B
\fBgetTabs(This) -> [integer()] when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns an array of tab stops, each expressed in tenths of a millimeter.

.PP
Each stop is measured from the left margin and therefore each value must be larger than the last.


.RE
.B
\fBgetTextColour(This) -> wx:wx_colour4() when This :: wxTextAttr().\fR

.br
.RS
